description:
In cli/triton-cli/src/output/table.rs, TableBuilder::add_row() accepts any-length Vec<String> without checking that it matches the header count. A row with too few or too many elements silently produces misaligned output. Should add a debug_assert_eq!(row.len(), expected) to catch mismatches during development:

    pub fn add_row(&mut self, row: Vec<String>) {
        let expected = self.long_headers.as_ref().unwrap_or(&self.headers).len();
        debug_assert_eq!(row.len(), expected, "row length must match header count");
        self.rows.push(row);
    }
